atharvaveda:Atharvaveda
a
rdfs:Class
rdfs:comment
Fourth Veda, containing the knowledge of atharvāṇas, the procedures of beliefs and rituals addressing practical issues of daily life of the Vedic society in Hinduism, compiled about 1200 to 1000 BC.
rdfs:isDefinedBy
atharvaveda:
skos:note
The Atharvaveda contains 20 Kandas.
rdfs:subClassOf
indology:Veda

atharvaveda:Paippalada-Samhita
a
rdfs:Class
rdfs:comment
One of the nine recensions of the Atharvaveda, along the different shakhas or Hindu theological schools, specialized in learning Vedic texts. Only this one and the Shaunakiya recension are extent.
rdfs:isDefinedBy
atharvaveda:
rdfs:subClassOf
